variables.value: Hey, got a minute?\nI've got a quick favor to ask.
Everyone loves a resort,\nyou stubborn kid.
Daddy built a ship, and it's coming to the port soon!\nHe said we can ride it next time. I'm sooo excited!
Sometimes scary old guys walk around here.\nI heard they hang out near the shipyard.
Tomorrow's lunch is hamburger steak,\nbut only Tristar elite kids get the kind with cheese inside!
I got invited on a cruise to Tokyo 'cause I'm a Tristar elite!\nI might get to see the Football Frontier too!
We went to a restaurant, and they gave me\na Crooked-Tail Cat Cookie just for being a Tristar elite!
Next time I'm volunteering at the port!\nThey said Tristar kids should set an example for everyone else!
I was watching a football match and something called a "Keshin"\nappeared! Can you guys do that too?
That football team with the scary guys?\nThey said their manager's a dog! Maybe he just barks the orders!
I worked so hard to build my dream house in a prime spot...\nbut the <LST:SAKURAZAKI>s' place across the street\nis in a whole different league.
Didn't the <LST:SAKURAZAKI> boy get into it with some delinquents?\nI caught a bit of it on our security cam...\nHonestly, I've been worried ever since.
Hillview's always been home to the rich—politicians, CEOs...\nEven the people just walking around look like celebrities.
The bigger the house, the more there is to clean...\nNext goal: get a housekeeper like the <LST:SAKURAZAKI>s.
But that might make\nfor harsh winters...
I'm thinking of remodeling to get a better ocean view. It'd be lovely\nin summer... but the sea breeze might make winter unbearable.
The flowers at Cupid's Carnival made me want to redo the garden.\nA yard like the <LST:SAKURAZAKI>s', with cherry blossoms in spring,\nwould be lovely.
My husband's been eyeing a car, and I'm on board...\nbut <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> is all hills and tight roads.\nA big bulky one just won't work here.
Of course that <LST:SAKURAZAKI> kid would make it to nationals.\nI want to give our child that kind of first-class environment too.
You've heard the rumors about turning the beach into a resort, right?\nMy son got all excited, saying,\n"I'd rather go there than fly overseas!"
My son said they might build a big mall in <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.\nHe was thrilled and said "More places to hang out with my friends!"
I heard the ones trying to shut down the shopping district\nhave been making trouble. Littering and such...\nEven my son was upset.
Have you heard what the new mall might look like?\nApparently they want to make it look like a castle!
The shopping district's been holding sales to fight\nback against the shutdown. I want to support them,\nso I've been going as often as I can.
So the <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> football team made it to nationals?\nEveryone in the Shopping District is thrilled!
The noodle shop was giving out discounts after <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> won!\nHaha, I just popped in by chance and lucked into a deal.
Oh, aren't you kids from <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>? Good luck in the finals!\nWe'll all be cheering with the folks from the Shopping District!
A rough-looking boy's been hanging around the <LST:SAKURAZAKI>s' lately.\nYou should be careful too.
I moved here for the peace and quiet...\nIf that resort gets built, it'll be noisy, and that worries me.
Well now, aren't you the <LST:SAKURAZAKI> boy?\nDon't get too wild, or your father will worry, you know.
I chose <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> for the calm...\nA big shopping center would just make it noisy.
I heard the pitch for the mall project...\nIt was all about money, so I couldn't get behind it.
It's probably outsiders stirring up all this talk about\nclosing the district. I just want to shop in peace, you know?
Looks like you're quite popular.\nI get you're having fun, but try not to cause a ruckus, alright?
What a shame... That kind of building doesn't suit <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.\nThis town's charm is in preserving what's old and good.
There's a bit of a divide now between those who want to keep\nthe district and those who don't. But most locals support keeping it.
You haven't gotten roped into that resort petition, have you?\nThose people can be a little pushy.
Lately the whole Shopping District's been in full cheer mode.\nThanks to you all, the town feels a little brighter.
I love the calm of <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>... taking the tram and strolling\naround the Shopping District now and then... That's the life I like.
<FST:CHINAMI> at the noodle shop is so dependable for a high schooler.\nEven rowdy customers don't faze her—it's impressive.
I love hunting for finds at Magic Moves.\nThe manager <FLC:ISHIURI>'s blunt, but she's got a great eye.
People are talking about <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> all over lately.\nEven if things are a bit noisy, that kind of energy doesn't bother me.
Rumor has it even the troublemakers have gotten into football.\nIf it calms the town down, I won't complain.
There might be\nsomething weird in it.
Just once,\nI want to ride it!
I'll be careful\nnot to get hurt!
I never imagined my only son would start acting like a delinquent...\nThis is exactly why I opposed that road to the Downtown disctrict.
My son has taken an interest in the port's food stalls.\nI told him I'd have our chef make the same dishes,\nbut he won't listen.
My son says he wants to play football, and I'm at my wit's end.\nDid one of those football club kids influence him?
My son won't stop insisting on riding the No. 9 West Bus alone.\nEven though our limo is faster and safer...
He's been playing football behind our backs.\nWe told him over and over,\n"If you're going to play something, choose a gentleman's sport."
My son keeps asking to join a football club.\nBut I can't stop worrying about him getting hurt.
His determination wore me down, so I finally let him join the club.\nThat trio of coordinators is a bit much...\nbut I think we can trust them.
I arranged for us to go see the grand finals—\nit'll be a learning experience for my son too.\nI'll have to get a bodyguard so we don't get separated in the crowd.
I'm just copying them, but Dad's such a worrywart.\nBesides, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI> 's really cool!
Oh, hey <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>!\nMan, I wish I could dress all cool like you!
A friend told me stall food tastes better somehow.\nI just have to find out what's so good about it!
You're all on the football team, right?\nTeach me how to play! I want to be a forward!
I want to take the bus to school, but Dad still says no.\nI wanna try pressing the button to get off!
I got to join the Seagulls Football Club practice!\nI even scored a goal, just like <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>!
Sure, injuries are scary, but playing with the club is so much fun!\nIf I just talk to Mom and Dad, they'll understand, right?
After joining the club, Dad gave me some\nlimited-edition CHAMP-ON spikes!\nOne day, I'm gonna go up against you guys wearing these!
Dad's taking me to the grand finals!\nPromise you'll win and show me that championship trophy!
I don't want to hear such foul language coming from my sweet boy!\nHe really isn't ready to leave the house yet.
We owe a lot to the <LST:SAKURAZAKI>s, but I must insist...\nPlease keep your distance from my son.
I can't trust food unless it's prepared by a top chef.\nYou never know what might be in food made outside the home!
Football's a sport where getting hurt is part of the deal!\nI just don't want my sweet boy to get hurt.
You never know who might get on the bus...\nIf it got hijacked or something, there'd be no coming back from that!
Watching your practice made him want to play too.\nHe's totally hooked now... Maybe there's no stopping him.
I want to support my son's wish to play football.\nI worry, but deep down I know I should let him play...
I believe he has what it takes to get into Raimon's club someday.\nI'm worried, but I've decided to support him no matter what.
Your parents are coming to watch the grand finals, right?\nTake care of yourselves and show them what you've got.
Many families around here have housekeepers,\nbut I hear <FST:NIIJIMA> at the <LST:SAKURAZAKI> house is absolutely impeccable.
Your housekeeper <FST:NIIJIMA> always seems to be waiting, looking worried.\nDo head home soon, won't you?
It's been a while since I saw <FST:SAKURAZAKI> in the company of friends.\nForgive the meddling, but I must say it was a relief.
I've heard <FST:SAKURAZAKI>'s father is quite the doting parent.\nI imagine he's watching these big matches from abroad, too.
The Tristar children are always volunteering, aren't they?\nSo young, yet so admirable. Truly impressive.
The Harborfront Bakery family lives on this very street.\nTheir shop's been making castella for 400 years.\nA legacy to be proud of.
I heard the lady next door recently replanted the trees in her garden.\nThe gardens here are all so lovely—they're a joy to stroll through.
I had a brief chat with <FST:NIIJIMA> the other day.\nShe looked positively delighted about <FST:SAKURAZAKI> making the finals.
Guys like <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>, coasting by comfortably without putting in the work?\nNot my style. I'm heading to a city university and expanding the family business!
Wh-what do you want?! If you've got no reason to be here,\njust go already! I'm nothing like you punks...!
Going against <FLC:YAGYU>, the politician's son? Are you out of your mind?\nDon't come crying if it tanks your college or job prospects...
So <FLC:YAGYU> and <FLC:GARYU> joined the football club too...?\nI used to think football was a joke,\nbut maybe I need to rethink things.
Honestly, I was pretty dismissive of the football team at first...\nbut now I'm rooting for you. You'd better make it to nationals!
Not bad at all so far.
Oh? A twist on\nthe shape, huh.
Sounds like a new\npath's opened up!
Where do you get your castella? It's got to be Harborfront, right?\nWe've got history that Heritage Breadworks just can't match.
Heritage Breadworks launched a castella collab with a hit anime.\nWe stick to flavor alone... but I'll admit, I'm curious.
Harborfront's castella is all about dedication to flavor.\nShowing our artisans at work—that's the best kind of promotion.
We've been running our logo at Nagasaki Civic Stadium lately.\nTurns out castella's actually useful for athlete nutrition, too.
Heritage Breadworks put out a souvenir-friendly castella.\nI want to honor tradition...\nbut maybe it's time we tried something new.
Caught the broadcast of <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>'s recent match.\nAs a local business, we're thinking about how we can support the team.
We want to support you somehow for the grand finals.\nLet us send over some castella! You just do your best out there!
